description: Ends the session. After you end a session, you can still access its content but you can't add to it. To delete the session and it's content, you use the DeleteSession API operation. For more information about sessions, see Store and retrieve conversation history and context with Amazon Bedrock sessions.

parameters.name: sessionIdentifier
parameters.description: The unique identifier for the session to end. You can specify either the session's sessionId or its Amazon Resource Name (ARN).

nested_items.name: sessionArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the session you ended.

nested_items.name: sessionId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the session you ended.

nested_items.name: sessionStatus
nested_items.description: The current status of the session you ended.
